<span id="ii.xiii-p36"></span> Chrysostom, VI. p. 171:  “As the day
brings man out to his work, so the night succeeding releases him from
his countless toils and thoughts, and lulling his weary eyes to sleep,
and closing their lids, prepares him to welcome the sunbeam again with
his force in full vigour.”

