id="ii.xiii-p36.1"></span>

<span id="ii.xiii-p37"></span> Clement of Alexandria (*Stromat*. IV. 22,
E. Tr.):  “And in this way they seem to have called the night Euphrone,
since then the soul released from the perceptions of sense turns in on
itself, and has a truer hold of intelligence (<span class="Greek"><span
id="ii.xiii-p37.1"></span>φρόνησις</span>).”

<span id="fn_1078"></span>[53:1079](2070025.htm#fr_1078.md) <span
